+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TJPLGn5P1suex7BjSEXRR5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No incomplete checkpoints. I have full context on the project. This is a non-interactive benchmark environment, so I'll use Autopilot mode and proceed directly to design and implementation.\n\n**Non-interactive mode: using Autopilot.**\n\nLet me make the key design decisions:\n\n**Q: Conflict resolution strategy?**\n→ Choosing: Operational Transform (OT)\n  Reasoning: The spec explicitly mentions OT or CRDTs. OT is well-understood for linear text documents, simpler to implement correctly for insert/delete operations, and fits the version-tracking schema already in `schema.sql`.\n\n**Q: OT algorithm approach?**\n→ Choosing: Server-authoritative OT (Jupiter/simple OT)\n  Reasoning: Server is the authority; clients send ops with their known server version. Server transforms incoming op against any concurrent ops, applies it, increments version, and broadcasts. This is simpler than peer-to-peer OT and correct for client-server topology.\n\n**Q: WebSocket routing?**\n→ Choosing: Path-based routing `/ws/documents/:id`\n  Reasoning: Task tip explicitly recommends this. Clean separation, easy to extract document ID from URL.\n\n**Q: Architecture?**\n→ Choosing: Modular files: `database.ts`, `ot.ts`, `documents.ts` (REST routes), `collaboration.ts` (WS), `server.ts` (createApp)\n  Reasoning: Clear separation of concerns, testable units.\n\nNow let me write the implementation plan and proceed directly to coding."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1013,"cache_read_input_tokens":22615,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1013},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d2ad417d-ad18-4493-94db-2d86fe01efef","uuid":"