+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NbsYd4pTTTuseMp6LeZbti","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VZBsbuSTdWyDgP9LCTnjTo","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-collaborative-editor.md","content":"# Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a collaborative real-time document editing server with REST API, WebSocket-based live collaboration, Operational Transform conflict resolution, and SQLite persistence.\n\n**Architecture:** Server-authoritative Operational Transform (OT): clients send ops tagged with their known server version; the server transforms incoming ops against any concurrent ops applied since that version, applies the transformed op, increments the document version, and broadcasts the canonical op to all other connected clients. Express handles REST; `ws` library handles WebSockets via path `/ws/documents/:id`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Express 4, ws 8, better-sqlite3 11, Vitest 2, supertest 7\n\n---\n\n## Module Layout\n\n```\nsrc/\n  database.ts        -- DB init, typed query helpers\n  ot.ts              -- OT types + transform logic\n  documents.ts       -- Express router (REST CRUD + history)\n  collaboration.ts   -- WebSocket upgrade handler + per-document rooms\n  server.ts          -- createApp() factory (exported entry point)\ntests/\n  ot.test.ts\n  documents.test.ts\n  collaboration.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Database Layer\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `schema.sql` (already exists, use as-is)\n- Create: `src/database.ts`\n- Create: `tests/database.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```typescript\n// tests/database.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { initDb, closeDb } from '../src/database.js';\nimport type { Database } from 'better-sqlite3';\n\ndescribe('database', () => {\n  let db: Database;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    db = initDb(':memory:');\n  });\n\n  afterEach(() => {\n    closeDb(db);\n  });\n\n  it('creates documents table', () => {\n    const row = db.prepare(\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table' AND name='documents'\").get();\n    expect(row).toBeTruthy();\n  });\n\n  it('creates versions table', () => {\n    const row = db.prepare(\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table' AND name='versions'\").get();\n    expect(row).toBeTruthy();\n  });\n\n  it('inserts and retrieves a document', () => {\n    db.prepare(\"INSERT INTO documents (id, title, content) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\").run('doc1', 'Test', 'hello');\n    const row = db.prepare(\"SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?\").get('doc1') as { title: string };\n    expect(row.title).toBe('Test');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/database.test.ts\n```\nExpected: FAIL with import error (module doesn't exist yet).\n\n**Step 3: Write implementation**\n\n```typescript\n// src/database.ts\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\nimport { dirname, join } from 'path';\n\nconst __dirname = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nexport function initDb(dbPath = 'collab.db'): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n  const schema = readFileSync(join(__dirname, '..', 'schema.sql'), 'utf-8');\n  db.exec(schema);\n  return db;\n}\n\nexport function closeDb(db: Database.Database): void {\n  db.close();\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/database.test.ts\n```\nExpected: PASS (3 tests).\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/database.ts tests/database.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: database layer with init and schema\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Operational Transform Core\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ot.ts`\n- Create: `tests/ot.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\n```typescript\n// tests/ot.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { applyOp, transformOp, type Op } from '../src/ot.js';\n\ndescribe('applyOp', () => {\n  it('inserts text at position', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello', { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' })).toBe('hello world');\n  });\n\n  it('inserts at start', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('world', { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'hello ' })).toBe('hello world');\n  });\n\n  it('deletes text at position', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello world', { type: 'delete', pos: 5, len: 6 })).toBe('hello');\n  });\n\n  it('deletes at start', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello', { type: 'delete', pos: 0, len: 5 })).toBe('');\n  });\n\n  it('rejects out-of-bounds insert', () => {\n    expect(() => applyOp('hi', { type: 'insert', pos: 10, text: 'x' })).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('rejects out-of-bounds delete', () => {\n    expect(() => applyOp('hi', { type: 'delete', pos: 0, len: 10 })).toThrow();\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - insert vs insert', () => {\n  // Two users insert simultaneously.\n  // User A inserts 'X' at pos 3. User B inserts 'Y' at pos 5.\n  // A's op arrives first at server. B's op must be transformed.\n  it('later insert shifts right when prior insert is before it', () => {\n    const priorInsert: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'X' };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'Y' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, priorInsert);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 6, text: 'Y' });\n  });\n\n  it('insert at same position: tie-break shifts the incoming right', () => {\n    const prior: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'X' };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'Y' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, prior);\n    // Prior already inserted at 3, so incoming shifts to 4\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 4, text: 'Y' });\n  });\n\n  it('incoming insert before prior insert: unchanged', () => {\n    const prior: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'X' };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'Y' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, prior);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'Y' });\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - delete vs insert', () => {\n  it('delete shifts right when prior insert is before it', () => {\n    const prior: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'XX' };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'delete', pos: 5, len: 3 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, prior);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 7, len: 3 });\n  });\n\n  it('delete start inside prior insert region: adjust to after insert', () => {\n    // Prior inserts 3 chars at pos 4. Incoming deletes starting at pos 4.\n    const prior: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 4, text: 'ABC' };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'delete', pos: 4, len: 2 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, prior);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 7, len: 2 });\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - insert vs delete', () => {\n  it('insert shifts left when prior delete is before it', () => {\n    const prior: Op = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, len: 3 };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 7, text: 'X' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, prior);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 4, text: 'X' });\n  });\n\n  it('insert inside deleted region: clamp to delete start', () => {\n    const prior: Op = { type: 'delete', pos: 3, len: 5 };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'X' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, prior);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'X' });\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - delete vs delete', () => {\n  it('later delete shifts left when prior delete is entirely before it', () => {\n    const prior: Op = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, len: 3 };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'delete', pos: 8, len: 2 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, prior);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 5, len: 2 });\n  });\n\n  it('overlapping deletes: trim incoming to non-deleted chars', () => {\n    // Prior deletes pos 3-7 (len 5). Incoming deletes pos 5-9 (len 5).\n    // After prior delete, chars at 5-7 are already gone.\n    // Remaining chars of incoming: 8-9 (2 chars), now shifted by -5 -> pos 3, len 2.\n    const prior: Op = { type: 'delete', pos: 3, len: 5 };\n    const incoming: Op = { type: 'delete', pos: 5, len: 5 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(incoming, prior);\n    expect((transformed as { type: 'delete'; pos: number; len: number }).len).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('convergence', () => {\n  it('two concurrent inserts converge to same string regardless of order', () => {\n    const doc = 'hello world';\n    const opA: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: '!' };\n    const opB: Op = { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: '>' };\n\n    // Server receives opA first\n    const docAfterA = applyOp(doc, opA);\n    const opB_transformed = transformOp(opB, opA);\n    const result1 = applyOp(docAfterA, opB_transformed);\n\n    // Server receives opB first\n    const docAfterB = applyOp(doc, opB);\n    const opA_transformed = transformOp(opA, opB);\n    const result2 = applyOp(docAfterB, opA_transformed);\n\n    expect(result1).toBe(result2);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/ot.test.ts\n```\nExpected: FAIL (module not found).\n\n**Step 3: Write implementation**\n\n```typescript\n// src/ot.ts\n\nexport type InsertOp = { type: 'insert'; pos: number; text: string };\nexport type DeleteOp = { type: 'delete'; pos: number; len: number };\nexport type Op = InsertOp | DeleteOp;\n\nexport function applyOp(content: string, op: Op): string {\n  if (op.type === 'insert') {\n    if (op.pos < 0 || op.pos > content.length) {\n      throw new Error(`Insert position ${op.pos} out of bounds (content length ${content.length})`);\n    }\n    return content.slice(0, op.pos) + op.text + content.slice(op.pos);\n  } else {\n    if (op.pos < 0 || op.pos + op.len > content.length) {\n      throw new Error(`Delete range [${op.pos}, ${op.pos + op.len}) out of bounds (content length ${content.length})`);\n    }\n    return content.slice(0, op.pos) + content.slice(op.pos + op.len);\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Transform `incoming` against `prior` (which has already been applied).\n * Returns a new op that achieves the same intent on the post-prior document.\n */\nexport function transformOp(incoming: Op, prior: Op): Op {\n  if (prior.type === 'insert' && incoming.type === 'insert') {\n    // If prior inserted before (or at same position), shift incoming right\n    if (prior.pos < incoming.pos || prior.pos === incoming.pos) {\n      return { ...incoming, pos: incoming.pos + prior.text.length };\n    }\n    return incoming;\n  }\n\n  if (prior.type === 'insert' && incoming.type === 'delete') {\n    const priorEnd = prior.pos + prior.text.length;\n    if (prior.pos <= incoming.pos) {\n      // Prior insert is before or at delete start: shift delete right\n      return { ...incoming, pos: incoming.pos + prior.text.length };\n    }\n    // Prior insert is within the delete range: we can ignore for position but\n    // the inserted text is now in the doc — don't delete it, adjust length\n    // This keeps delete intent: just shift start isn't needed (prior.pos > incoming.pos)\n    return incoming;\n  }\n\n  if (prior.type === 'delete' && incoming.type === 'insert') {\n    const priorEnd = prior.pos + prior.len;\n    if (incoming.pos <= prior.pos) {\n      // Insert is before the deletion: unchanged\n      return incoming;\n    }\n    if (incoming.pos >= priorEnd) {\n      // Insert is after the deletion: shift left by deleted amount\n      return { ...incoming, pos: incoming.pos - prior.len };\n    }\n    // Insert is inside the deleted region: clamp to deletion start\n    return { ...incoming, pos: prior.pos };\n  }\n\n  if (prior.type === 'delete' && incoming.type === 'delete') {\n    const priorEnd = prior.pos + prior.len;\n    const incomingEnd = incoming.pos + incoming.len;\n\n    if (incomingEnd <= prior.pos) {\n      // Incoming delete is entirely before prior: unchanged\n      return incoming;\n    }\n    if (incoming.pos >= priorEnd) {\n      // Incoming delete is entirely after prior: shift left\n      return { ...incoming, pos: incoming.pos - prior.len };\n    }\n    // Overlapping deletes: trim the overlap\n    const newPos = Math.min(incoming.pos, prior.pos);\n    // Calculate how many chars of incoming are outside the prior deleted region\n    const overlapStart = Math.max(incoming.pos, prior.pos);\n    const overlapEnd = Math.min(incomingEnd, priorEnd);\n    const overlap = Math.max(0, overlapEnd - overlapStart);\n    const newLen = Math.max(0, incoming.len - overlap - (prior.pos < incoming.pos ? prior.pos + prior.len - incoming.pos : 0));\n    // Simpler approach: remaining chars = (chars before prior) + (chars after prior within incoming)\n    const beforePrior = Math.max(0, prior.pos - incoming.pos);\n    const afterPrior = Math.max(0, incomingEnd - priorEnd);\n    const finalLen = beforePrior + afterPrior;\n    const finalPos = Math.min(incoming.pos, prior.pos);\n    if (finalLen === 0) {\n      // Entire incoming delete region was already deleted: no-op delete\n      return { type: 'delete', pos: finalPos, len: 0 };\n    }\n    return { type: 'delete', pos: finalPos, len: finalLen };\n  }\n\n  return incoming;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/ot.test.ts\n```\nExpected: All pass. If convergence test fails, revisit transform logic.\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ot.ts tests/ot.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: operational transform core (insert/delete)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: REST API for Documents\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/documents.ts`\n- Create: `tests/documents.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests**\n\n```typescript\n// tests/documents.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../src/server.js';\n\ndescribe('REST API', () => {\n  let app: ReturnType<typeof createApp>;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    app = createApp(':memory:');\n  });\n\n  afterEach(async () => {\n    await app.stop();\n  });\n\n  it('POST /documents creates a document', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'My Doc', content: 'Hello' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('My Doc');\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('Hello');\n    expect(res.body.version).toBe(0);\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents lists all documents', async () => {\n    await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Doc A', content: '' });\n    await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Doc B', content: '' });\n    const res = await request(app.app).get('/documents');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id returns a document', async () => {\n    const create = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Doc', content: 'hi' });\n    const id = create.body.id;\n    const res = await request(app.app).get(`/documents/${id}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('hi');\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id returns 404 for unknown id', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app.app).get('/documents/nonexistent');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n\n  it('PUT /documents/:id updates title', async () => {\n    const create = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Old', content: '' });\n    const id = create.body.id;\n    const res = await request(app.app).put(`/documents/${id}`).send({ title: 'New' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('New');\n  });\n\n  it('DELETE /documents/:id removes document', async () => {\n    const create = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Del', content: '' });\n    const id = create.body.id;\n    await request(app.app).delete(`/documents/${id}`);\n    const res = await request(app.app).get(`/documents/${id}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id/history returns version history', async () => {\n    const create = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Doc', content: 'abc' });\n    const id = create.body.id;\n    const res = await request(app.app).get(`/documents/${id}/history`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body)).toBe(true);\n  });\n\n  it('POST /documents rejects missing title', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ content: 'hi' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/documents.test.ts\n```\nExpected: FAIL (server.ts not found).\n\n**Step 3: Write documents router**\n\n```typescript\n// src/documents.ts\nimport { Router } from 'express';\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\nimport type { Database } from 'better-sqlite3';\n\ninterface DocRow {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;\n  version: number;\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface VersionRow {\n  id: number;\n  document_id: string;\n  version: number;\n  content: string;\n  operation: string | null;\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\nexport function createDocumentsRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // Helper: get current doc version (max version from versions table, default -1 => 0 docs have ver 0 after creation)\n  function getDocVersion(docId: string): number {\n    const row = db.prepare('SELECT COALESCE(MAX(version), -1) as v FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?').get(docId) as { v: number };\n    return row.v + 1; // version count = max_version + 1 BUT we store version 0 on create\n    // Actually: version = current number stored in versions table max\n  }\n\n  // POST /documents\n  router.post('/', (req, res) => {\n    const { title, content = '' } = req.body as { title?: string; content?: string };\n    if (!title || typeof title !== 'string' || title.trim() === '') {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'title is required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = randomUUID();\n    const now = new Date().toISOString();\n    db.prepare('INSERT INTO documents (id, title, content, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)').run(id, title.trim(), content, now, now);\n    // Record version 0\n    db.prepare('INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation) VALUES (?, 0, ?, NULL)').run(id, content);\n    res.status(201).json({ id, title: title.trim(), content, version: 0, created_at: now, updated_at: now });\n  });\n\n  // GET /documents\n  router.get('/', (_req, res) => {\n    const docs = db.prepare('SELECT id, title, content, created_at, updated_at FROM documents ORDER BY created_at DESC').all() as DocRow[];\n    // Attach current version to each\n    const result = docs.map(doc => {\n      const vRow = db.prepare('SELECT COALESCE(MAX(version), 0) as v FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?').get(doc.id) as { v: number };\n      return { ...doc, version: vRow.v };\n    });\n    res.json(result);\n  });\n\n  // GET /documents/:id\n  router.get('/:id', (req, res) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT id, title, content, created_at, updated_at FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id) as DocRow | undefined;\n    if (!doc) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    const vRow = db.prepare('SELECT COALESCE(MAX(version), 0) as v FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?').get(doc.id) as { v: number };\n    res.json({ ...doc, version: vRow.v });\n  });\n\n  // PUT /documents/:id\n  router.put('/:id', (req, res) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT id FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id) as { id: string } | undefined;\n    if (!doc) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    const { title } = req.body as { title?: string };\n    if (title !== undefined && (typeof title !== 'string' || title.trim() === '')) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'title must be non-empty string' }); return;\n    }\n    const now = new Date().toISOString();\n    if (title) {\n      db.prepare('UPDATE documents SET title = ?, updated_at = ? WHERE id = ?').run(title.trim(), now, req.params.id);\n    }\n    const updated = db.prepare('SELECT id, title, content, created_at, updated_at FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id) as DocRow;\n    const vRow = db.prepare('SELECT COALESCE(MAX(version), 0) as v FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?').get(req.params.id) as { v: number };\n    res.json({ ...updated, version: vRow.v });\n  });\n\n  // DELETE /documents/:id\n  router.delete('/:id', (req, res) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT id FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id) as { id: string } | undefined;\n    if (!doc) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    db.prepare('DELETE FROM documents WHERE id = ?').run(req.params.id);\n    res.status(204).send();\n  });\n\n  // GET /documents/:id/history\n  router.get('/:id/history', (req, res) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT id FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id) as { id: string } | undefined;\n    if (!doc) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    const versions = db.prepare('SELECT id, document_id, version, content, operation, created_at FROM versions WHERE document_id = ? ORDER BY version ASC').all(req.params.id) as VersionRow[];\n    res.json(versions.map(v => ({ ...v, operation: v.operation ? JSON.parse(v.operation) : null })));\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Write the server factory (partial — WebSocket added in Task 4)**\n\n```typescript\n// src/server.ts\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createServer, type Server } from 'http';\nimport { initDb, closeDb } from './database.js';\nimport { createDocumentsRouter } from './documents.js';\nimport type { Database } from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface AppInstance {\n  app: express.Application;\n  httpServer: Server;\n  db: Database.Database;\n  start(port?: number): Promise<number>;\n  stop(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): AppInstance {\n  const db = initDb(dbPath ?? 'collab.db');\n  const expressApp = express();\n  expressApp.use(express.json());\n  expressApp.use('/documents', createDocumentsRouter(db));\n\n  const httpServer = createServer(expressApp);\n\n  return {\n    app: expressApp,\n    httpServer,\n    db,\n    start(port = 0): Promise<number> {\n      return new Promise((resolve) => {\n        httpServer.listen(port, () => {\n          const addr = httpServer.address();\n          resolve(typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : port);\n        });\n      });\n    },\n    stop(): Promise<void> {\n      return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n        httpServer.close((err) => {\n          closeDb(db);\n          if (err) reject(err);\n          else resolve();\n        });\n      });\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/documents.test.ts\n```\nExpected: All pass.\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/documents.ts src/server.ts tests/documents.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: REST API for document CRUD and history\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: WebSocket Collaboration + OT Server\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/collaboration.ts`\n- Modify: `src/server.ts` (add WS upgrade handling)\n- Create: `tests/collaboration.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Tasks 1, 2, 3\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests**\n\n```typescript\n// tests/collaboration.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { createApp } from '../src/server.js';\nimport WebSocket from 'ws';\nimport request from 'supertest';\n\nfunction wsConnect(port: number, docId: string): Promise<WebSocket> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/ws/documents/${docId}`);\n    ws.once('open', () => resolve(ws));\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction nextMessage(ws: WebSocket): Promise<unknown> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    ws.once('message', (data) => {\n      try { resolve(JSON.parse(data.toString())); }\n      catch (e) { reject(e); }\n    });\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction waitFor(ws: WebSocket, predicate: (msg: unknown) => boolean, timeout = 3000): Promise<unknown> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const timer = setTimeout(() => reject(new Error('waitFor timeout')), timeout);\n    function onMessage(data: Buffer) {\n      try {\n        const msg = JSON.parse(data.toString());\n        if (predicate(msg)) {\n          clearTimeout(timer);\n          ws.off('message', onMessage);\n          resolve(msg);\n        }\n      } catch {}\n    }\n    ws.on('message', onMessage);\n  });\n}\n\ndescribe('WebSocket collaboration', () => {\n  let appInstance: ReturnType<typeof createApp>;\n  let port: number;\n  let docId: string;\n  const clients: WebSocket[] = [];\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    appInstance = createApp(':memory:');\n    port = await appInstance.start(0);\n    const res = await request(appInstance.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Test Doc', content: 'hello' });\n    docId = res.body.id;\n  });\n\n  afterEach(async () => {\n    for (const ws of clients) {\n      if (ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) ws.close();\n    }\n    clients.length = 0;\n    await appInstance.stop();\n  });\n\n  it('sends sync message on connect', async () => {\n    const ws = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n    clients.push(ws);\n    const msg = await nextMessage(ws) as { type: string; content: string; version: number };\n    expect(msg.type).toBe('sync');\n    expect(msg.content).toBe('hello');\n    expect(msg.version).toBe(0);\n    ws.close();\n  });\n\n  it('rejects connection to unknown document', async () => {\n    const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/ws/documents/nonexistent`);\n    clients.push(ws);\n    await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {\n      ws.once('close', () => resolve());\n      ws.once('error', () => resolve());\n    });\n    expect(ws.readyState).not.toBe(WebSocket.OPEN);\n  });\n\n  it('applies insert operation and broadcasts to other clients', async () => {\n    const ws1 = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n    clients.push(ws1);\n    await nextMessage(ws1); // sync\n\n    const ws2 = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n    clients.push(ws2);\n    await nextMessage(ws2); // sync\n\n    const op = { type: 'op', version: 0, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' } };\n    ws1.send(JSON.stringify(op));\n\n    const ack = await nextMessage(ws1) as { type: string };\n    expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    const broadcast = await nextMessage(ws2) as { type: string; op: { type: string } };\n    expect(broadcast.type).toBe('op');\n    expect(broadcast.op.type).toBe('insert');\n    ws1.close();\n    ws2.close();\n  });\n\n  it('two concurrent inserts converge', async () => {\n    const ws1 = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n    clients.push(ws1);\n    await nextMessage(ws1); // sync\n\n    const ws2 = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n    clients.push(ws2);\n    await nextMessage(ws2); // sync\n\n    // Both send ops against version 0 (concurrent)\n    const op1 = { type: 'op', version: 0, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'A' } };\n    const op2 = { type: 'op', version: 0, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'B' } };\n\n    ws1.send(JSON.stringify(op1));\n    ws2.send(JSON.stringify(op2));\n\n    // Wait for both to receive ack or broadcast\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));\n\n    // Check final content via REST\n    const res = await request(appInstance.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    const finalContent = res.body.content as string;\n    // Both 'A' and 'B' must be present\n    expect(finalContent).toContain('A');\n    expect(finalContent).toContain('B');\n    expect(finalContent).toContain('hello');\n  });\n\n  it('rejects malformed operation', async () => {\n    const ws = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n    clients.push(ws);\n    await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: 0, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 9999, text: 'x' } }));\n    const errMsg = await nextMessage(ws) as { type: string; error: string };\n    expect(errMsg.type).toBe('error');\n    expect(errMsg.error).toBeTruthy();\n  });\n\n  it('handles 10 concurrent clients', async () => {\n    const NUM = 10;\n    const sockets: WebSocket[] = [];\n    for (let i = 0; i < NUM; i++) {\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n      clients.push(ws);\n      sockets.push(ws);\n      await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n    }\n    // Each sends a unique insert\n    for (let i = 0; i < NUM; i++) {\n      sockets[i].send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: i === 0 ? 0 : 0, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: `${i}` } }));\n    }\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));\n    const res = await request(appInstance.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    // All digits 0-9 should appear in content (or at least no crash)\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    for (let i = 0; i < NUM; i++) {\n      sockets[i].close();\n    }\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/collaboration.test.ts\n```\n\n**Step 3: Write collaboration module**\n\n```typescript\n// src/collaboration.ts\nimport { WebSocketServer, WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport type { IncomingMessage } from 'http';\nimport type { Database } from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { applyOp, transformOp, type Op } from './ot.js';\n\ninterface ClientMessage {\n  type: 'op';\n  version: number;\n  op: Op;\n}\n\ninterface ServerOpMessage {\n  type: 'op';\n  version: number;\n  op: Op;\n}\n\ninterface SyncMessage {\n  type: 'sync';\n  content: string;\n  version: number;\n}\n\ninterface AckMessage {\n  type: 'ack';\n  version: number;\n}\n\ninterface ErrorMessage {\n  type: 'error';\n  error: string;\n}\n\ninterface OpsRow {\n  version: number;\n  content: string;\n  operation: string | null;\n}\n\ninterface DocRow {\n  id: string;\n  content: string;\n}\n\n// Per-document room: holds connected clients and serializes operations\nclass DocumentRoom {\n  private clients = new Set<WebSocket>();\n  private mutex = false;\n  private queue: Array<() => void> = [];\n\n  constructor(\n    private docId: string,\n    private db: Database.Database,\n  ) {}\n\n  addClient(ws: WebSocket): void {\n    this.clients.add(ws);\n    ws.once('close', () => this.clients.delete(ws));\n  }\n\n  removeClient(ws: WebSocket): void {\n    this.clients.delete(ws);\n  }\n\n  getCurrentVersion(): number {\n    const row = this.db.prepare('SELECT COALESCE(MAX(version), 0) as v FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?').get(this.docId) as { v: number };\n    return row.v;\n  }\n\n  getCurrentContent(): string {\n    const row = this.db.prepare('SELECT content FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(this.docId) as DocRow | undefined;\n    return row?.content ?? '';\n  }\n\n  /** Apply an incoming op atomically, with OT transformation against concurrent ops */\n  applyClientOp(clientVersion: number, op: Op): { newVersion: number; transformedOp: Op } {\n    // Get all ops applied since clientVersion\n    const concurrentOps = this.db\n      .prepare('SELECT version, operation FROM versions WHERE document_id = ? AND version > ? ORDER BY version ASC')\n      .all(this.docId, clientVersion) as { version: number; operation: string | null }[];\n\n    // Transform incoming op against each concurrent op\n    let transformedOp: Op = op;\n    for (const row of concurrentOps) {\n      if (row.operation) {\n        const priorOp = JSON.parse(row.operation) as Op;\n        transformedOp = transformOp(transformedOp, priorOp);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply to current content\n    const currentContent = this.getCurrentContent();\n    const newContent = applyOp(currentContent, transformedOp);\n\n    const newVersion = this.getCurrentVersion() + 1;\n    const now = new Date().toISOString();\n\n    // Persist: update doc content + record version\n    this.db.prepare('UPDATE documents SET content = ?, updated_at = ? WHERE id = ?').run(newContent, now, this.docId);\n    this.db.prepare('INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)').run(\n      this.docId, newVersion, newContent, JSON.stringify(transformedOp)\n    );\n\n    return { newVersion, transformedOp };\n  }\n\n  broadcast(sender: WebSocket, msg: ServerOpMessage): void {\n    const payload = JSON.stringify(msg);\n    for (const client of this.clients) {\n      if (client !== sender && client.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n        client.send(payload);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  get size(): number {\n    return this.clients.size;\n  }\n}\n\nexport function attachWebSocket(\n  wss: WebSocketServer,\n  db: Database.Database,\n): void {\n  const rooms = new Map<string, DocumentRoom>();\n\n  function getRoom(docId: string): DocumentRoom {\n    let room = rooms.get(docId);\n    if (!room) {\n      room = new DocumentRoom(docId, db);\n      rooms.set(docId, room);\n    }\n    return room;\n  }\n\n  wss.on('connection', (ws: WebSocket, req: IncomingMessage) => {\n    // Extract document ID from path: /ws/documents/:id\n    const match = req.url?.match(/^\\/ws\\/documents\\/([^/?]+)/);\n    if (!match) {\n      ws.close(1008, 'Invalid path');\n      return;\n    }\n    const docId = match[1];\n\n    // Verify document exists\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT id, content FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(docId) as DocRow | undefined;\n    if (!doc) {\n      ws.close(1008, 'Document not found');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const room = getRoom(docId);\n    room.addClient(ws);\n\n    // Send initial sync\n    const syncMsg: SyncMessage = {\n      type: 'sync',\n      content: room.getCurrentContent(),\n      version: room.getCurrentVersion(),\n    };\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify(syncMsg));\n\n    ws.on('message', (data) => {\n      let msg: ClientMessage;\n      try {\n        msg = JSON.parse(data.toString()) as ClientMessage;\n      } catch {\n        const err: ErrorMessage = { type: 'error', error: 'Invalid JSON' };\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify(err));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      if (msg.type !== 'op') {\n        const err: ErrorMessage = { type: 'error', error: `Unknown message type: ${msg.type}` };\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify(err));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      if (!msg.op || !msg.op.type) {\n        const err: ErrorMessage = { type: 'error', error: 'Missing op' };\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify(err));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Validate op fields\n      const op = msg.op;\n      if (op.type === 'insert' && (typeof op.pos !== 'number' || typeof op.text !== 'string')) {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', error: 'Invalid insert op fields' } as ErrorMessage));\n        return;\n      }\n      if (op.type === 'delete' && (typeof op.pos !== 'number' || typeof op.len !== 'number')) {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', error: 'Invalid delete op fields' } as ErrorMessage));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      try {\n        const { newVersion, transformedOp } = room.applyClientOp(msg.version, op);\n\n        const ack: AckMessage = { type: 'ack', version: newVersion };\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify(ack));\n\n        const broadcast: ServerOpMessage = { type: 'op', version: newVersion, op: transformedOp };\n        room.broadcast(ws, broadcast);\n      } catch (err) {\n        const errMsg: ErrorMessage = { type: 'error', error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err) };\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify(errMsg));\n      }\n    });\n\n    ws.on('close', () => {\n      room.removeClient(ws);\n      if (room.size === 0) {\n        rooms.delete(docId);\n      }\n    });\n  });\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Update server.ts to wire WebSocket**\n\n```typescript\n// src/server.ts (updated)\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createServer, type Server } from 'http';\nimport { WebSocketServer } from 'ws';\nimport { initDb, closeDb } from './database.js';\nimport { createDocumentsRouter } from './documents.js';\nimport { attachWebSocket } from './collaboration.js';\nimport type { Database } from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface AppInstance {\n  app: express.Application;\n  httpServer: Server;\n  db: Database.Database;\n  start(port?: number): Promise<number>;\n  stop(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): AppInstance {\n  const db = initDb(dbPath ?? 'collab.db');\n  const expressApp = express();\n  expressApp.use(express.json());\n  expressApp.use('/documents', createDocumentsRouter(db));\n\n  const httpServer = createServer(expressApp);\n  const wss = new WebSocketServer({ server: httpServer, path: undefined });\n\n  // Filter upgrades to /ws/documents/* path\n  httpServer.on('upgrade', (req, socket, head) => {\n    if (req.url?.startsWith('/ws/documents/')) {\n      wss.handleUpgrade(req, socket as import('net').Socket, head, (ws) => {\n        wss.emit('connection', ws, req);\n      });\n    } else {\n      socket.destroy();\n    }\n  });\n\n  attachWebSocket(wss, db);\n\n  const openSockets = new Set<WebSocket>();\n\n  return {\n    app: expressApp,\n    httpServer,\n    db,\n    start(port = 0): Promise<number> {\n      return new Promise((resolve) => {\n        httpServer.listen(port, () => {\n          const addr = httpServer.address();\n          resolve(typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : port);\n        });\n      });\n    },\n    stop(): Promise<void> {\n      return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n        wss.clients.forEach(client => client.close());\n        wss.close(() => {\n          httpServer.close((err) => {\n            closeDb(db);\n            if (err) reject(err);\n            else resolve();\n          });\n        });\n      });\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/collaboration.test.ts\n```\n\n**Step 6: Run all tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\nExpected: All tests pass.\n\n**Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/collaboration.ts src/server.ts tests/collaboration.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: WebSocket collaboration with OT conflict resolution\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Build + Lint Verification\n\n**Files:** None new\n\n**Dependencies:** Tasks 1-4\n\n**Step 1: Run build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\nExpected: Compiles to `dist/` with no errors.\n\n**Step 2: Run lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\nFix any ESLint errors reported.\n\n**Step 3: Run all tests one more time**\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\nExpected: All tests pass.\n\n**Step 4: Final commit if any fixes needed**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"fix: lint and build issues\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Execution Wave Summary\n\n| Wave | Tasks | Can run in parallel? |\n|------|-------|---------------------|\n| 1 | Task 1 (DB), Task 2 (OT) | Yes |\n| 2 | Task 3 (REST + server.ts) | After Wave 1 |\n| 3 | Task 4 (WebSocket) | After Wave 2 |\n| 4 | Task 5 (build/lint) | After Wave 3 |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":202,"cache_read_input_tokens":25629,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"eph